messages.message:
Hey all, just wanted to cross post this! For any cypress tests that you own, you can now link them to a testmo case via the automated testing workflow!

This means that *all cypress tests* *should be linked to a testmo test case* and should have the automation test linking — this will allow us to track the stability of cypress tests within Testmo itself. Please let me or @youngmok.cho know if there are questions around this — the goal is to have consistency for how we track our test cases and manage what is covered by automated test vs requiring manual testing
